  <name>VSDView</name>
  <summary>Read-only viewer for Microsoft Visio files</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      VSDView is a lightweight viewer for Microsoft Visio files (.vsdx, .vsd, .vstx, .vss, .vssx),
      built with GTK4 and libadwaita. It renders diagrams using a built-in .vsdx parser with
      support for shapes, connectors, embedded images, gradients, text, stencils, themes, and
      multi-page documents. Optional libvisio support for legacy .vsd files.
    </p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Multi-page tab view</li>
      <li>Text search (Ctrl+F)</li>
      <li>PDF and text export</li>
      <li>Canvas background toggle (system/light/dark)</li>
      <li>Visio theme color support (DrawingML)</li>
      <li>Layer visibility</li>
      <li>Zoom-to-fit</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  <url type="homepage">https://github.com/yeager/vsdview</url>
  <url type="bugtracker">https://github.com/yeager/vsdview/issues</url>
